      <h2>Safety</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Read all safety warnings and all instructions.</strong> Failure to follow the warnings and instructions may result in electric shock, fire, and/or serious injury. Save all warnings and instructions for future reference.
      </div>

      <h3>Tool-Specific Safety Rules</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Hold the power tool by insulated gripping surfaces only, because the cutter may contact its own cord. Cutting a live wire may make exposed metal parts of the power tool live and could give the operator an electric shock.</li>
        <li>The tools must not be operated without the guide frame, as the rotating cutter is otherwise freely accessible.</li>
        <li>When starting up, hold the machine firmly. High torque at the cutter can cause the machine to twist.</li>
        <li>Keep hands away from the cutting area. Never reach under the workpiece. Contact with the rotating cutter can cause injury.</li>
        <li>Only insert the machine in the workpiece with the cutter running at full speed.</li>
        <li>Never use the machine when the cable is damaged. Do not touch a damaged cable and disconnect the mains plug if the cable is damaged during work.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Wear ear protection.</strong> Sound pressure level: 84 dB(A). Sound power level: 95 dB(A). Uncertainty K = 3 dB. Vibration emission a<sub>h</sub> = 3.0 m/s&sup2;, K = 1.5 m/s&sup2;.
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Wear a P2 protective mask</strong> to protect your health from dust generated during operation.
      </div>

