      <h2>Power Supply and Start-Up</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        The mains voltage must correspond to the specification on the rating plate. Always switch the machine off before connecting or disconnecting the mains lead.
      </div>

      <p>See the diagrams at the beginning of the manual for connection and disconnection of the power cable. To switch on, push the switch [1-1] forwards until it engages. Press the back end of the switch to release the switch-on lock and switch the machine off.</p>

      <h2>Machine Settings</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Always remove the power supply plug from the socket before carrying out any work on the machine.
      </div>

      <h3>Changing the Cutter</h3>
      <p>Required tool: fork wrench A/F 8 (supplied).</p>

      <div class="warning">
        Always wear protective gloves during tool change due to the risk of injury from the sharp cutter edges.
      </div>

      <h4>Removing the cutter</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Lift the unlocking lever [4-2] until it audibly engages with the fork wrench [4-1].</li>
        <li>Separate the motor unit [4-5] and the guide frame [4-4].</li>
        <li>Press and hold in the spindle lock [5-1].</li>
        <li>Release and unscrew the jointer bit [5-2] with the fork wrench.</li>
        <li>Release the spindle lock.</li>
      </ol>

      <h4>Inserting the cutter</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Before inserting a new jointer bit, ensure the machine, guide frame, and cutter shaft are free of chips and dust.</li>
        <li>Screw the jointer bit [5-2] onto the drive shaft and tighten with the fork wrench while holding the spindle lock [5-1].</li>
        <li>Slide the motor unit back into the guide frame until the unlocking lever [4-2] audibly engages.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Setting Jointing Depth</h3>
      <p>The jointing depth is set using the notch lever [1-7]. Press the notch lever lock [1-8] and swing the lever to the desired depth position. Available depth settings: 12, 15, 20, 25, and 28 mm.</p>

      <h3>Setting Jointing Height</h3>
      <h4>a) Centered on material thickness</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Push the slide [6-6] toward the front section of the guide frame.</li>
        <li>Set the material thickness using the selection slide [1-6].</li>
        <li>The jointing height is now automatically centred on the selected material thickness.</li>
      </ol>

      <h4>b) Freely selectable</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Release the clamping lever [6-1] for jointing height adjustment.</li>
        <li>Using the additional handle [6-2], raise the front section of the guide frame.</li>
        <li>Push the slide [6-6] to the stop in the direction of the motor unit.</li>
        <li>Set the desired jointing height using the scale [6-3] by moving the front section of the guide frame vertically.</li>
        <li>Close the clamping lever [6-1].</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Setting the Angle Guide</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Release the clamping lever for the angle guide [6-4].</li>
        <li>Set the desired angle using the scale [6-5]: steplessly from 0&deg;&ndash;90&deg;, or in notches at 0&deg;, 22.5&deg;, 45&deg;, 67.5&deg;, and 90&deg;.</li>
        <li>Close the clamping lever [6-4].</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        For mitre cutting thin workpieces: set the desired angle, release the clamping lever [6-1], push the slide [6-6] to the stop in the direction of the motor unit, slide the angle stop all the way down, then close the clamping lever [6-1]. Always release clamp lever [6-1] before resetting the angle stop.
      </div>

      <h3>Setting Dowel-Hole Width</h3>

      <div class="warning">
        Reliable setting of the dowel-hole width with the rotary switch [1-2] is only possible with the machine running.
      </div>

      <p>Three dowel-hole width settings are available:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>13 mm + cutter diameter</li>
        <li>19 mm + cutter diameter</li>
        <li>23 mm + cutter diameter</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Dust Extraction</h3>

      <div class="warning">
        Always connect the machine to a dust extractor. Connect a Festool extractor with an extractor hose diameter of 27 mm to the extraction nozzle [2-2].
      </div>

      <h3>Additional Stop with Extension</h3>
      <p>The additional stop [8-1] enlarges the contact surface when jointing on the workpiece edge, providing safer guidance. The distance to the centre of the routed hole can be reduced from 37 mm to 20 mm using the two integral stop spacers [8-6], allowing you to position the dowel closer to the edge.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Secure the additional stop to the threaded bores [8-3] on the guide frame using both screws [8-2]. The contact areas of the support ring [8-5] and the table [8-4] must be flush.</li>
        <li>The additional stop can be extended with the stop extension [8-7].</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Operation</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Always use the stop latches [2-4] and press the machine firmly onto the workpiece when jointing. The cutter oscillates laterally, which means the machine can shift on the workpiece if not properly secured.
      </div>

      <h3>Procedure for Creating a Dowelled Joint</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Select a Domino dowel and insert a matching cutter in the Domino jointer (see Changing the Cutter above).</li>
        <li>Set the jointing depth. The jointing depth must be at least 3 mm smaller than the workpiece thickness so that the dowelled joint is supportable.</li>
        <li>Set the jointing height to correspond to the workpiece thickness.</li>
        <li>Mark the areas on the workpiece that belong together [10-1] so that you can join them correctly after cutting the dowel holes.</li>
        <li>Position the two workpieces to be joined against one another and mark the desired positions of the dowels with a pencil [10-2].</li>
        <li>Set the desired dowel-hole width.</li>
        <li>Cut the dowel holes:
          <ol type="a">
            <li>Cut the first dowel hole by placing the stop latch at the side edge of the workpiece.</li>
            <li>Cut the following dowel holes according to the pencil markings and the scale of the viewing window [10-3].</li>
          </ol>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Recommended practice:</strong> Cut the first hole without play (dowel-hole width = Domino dowel width), and the remaining dowel holes to the next largest dowel-hole width. The first dowel hole serves as a reference dimension, while the remaining holes have tolerance for manufacturing inaccuracies.
      </div>

