      <h2>Maintenance and Care</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Always remove the power supply plug from the socket before carrying out any work on the machine. All maintenance and repair work which requires the motor casing to be opened may only be carried out by an authorised service centre.
      </div>

      <p>The Domino jointer is to a large extent maintenance-free. However, Festool recommends an annual inspection and/or a check after approximately 100 operating hours at an authorised customer service workshop. Use only original Festool spare parts.</p>

      <div class="note">
        Customer service and repair: contact Festool or an authorised service workshop. Find the nearest address at <a href="https://www.festool.com/Service" target="_blank">www.festool.com/Service</a>.
      </div>

      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Problem</th><th>Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Burns on workpiece</td>
            <td>Blunt jointer bit</td>
            <td>Use a sharp jointer bit</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Expansion of dowel hole</td>
            <td>Jointing depth excessive (greater than 20 mm) with 5 mm jointing bit</td>
            <td>Reduce jointing depth</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Dowel penetrates workpiece</td>
            <td>Incorrect workpiece thickness and/or jointing depth</td>
            <td>Adapt workpiece thickness and/or jointing depth</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tears at edge of dowel hole</td>
            <td>Excessive feed rate</td>
            <td>Reduce feed rate</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Dowel hole not parallel to workpiece edge</td>
            <td>Workpiece shifted during processing</td>
            <td>Secure workpiece properly</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Dowel hole not at right angles (90&deg;) to workpiece surface</td>
            <td>a) Deposits (e.g. chips) below the base plate<br/>b) Angle guide not set exactly to 90&deg;<br/>c) Worked without additional stop</td>
            <td>a) Remove deposits<br/>b) Set angle guide to 90&deg; exactly<br/>c) Use additional stop</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Position of dowel holes created with left and right stop latch does not exactly match</td>
            <td>The midpoint between the two stop latches is not exactly in the midpoint of the swivel range of the jointer bit</td>
            <td>Remove one of the stop latches [9-1]. Attach one of the accompanying narrower stop latches [9-2] to the dowel jointer, which allows more accurate adjustments.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

